This paper is about machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category for this paper. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as mutation and metamorphic testing, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses post-processing techniques, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of its approach using automatic consistency metrics, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach for repairing inconsistencies in machine translation, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
